Two forces were measured and recorded from the digital display of the slip-peel tester. The first, “Static Peak force” is generated as movement of the eggshell is initiated, i.e., it is the force required to release the grip of the tube of glue-like fixative that holds the eggshell in place on the hair (
 Fig. 2). Subsequently, as the glue tube slides along the hair some friction is generated that is averaged out by the device resulting in an “Average force” measurement (
 Fig. 2). Previous studies showed that the average force could be reduced by simple lubricants but Static Peak force was not significantly affected by any chemical treatments (
 Burgess, 2010; 
 Lapeere et al., 2014; 
 Ortega-Insaurralde et al., 2014).
